request.description:
`Deprecated`: This endpoint is now used exclusively for development
purposes to acquire an authentication token.
It bypasses the standard application login process and directly authenticates users
from this call.
The primary objective is to test new IBM i user profiles and verify
their access to the database, as these profiles will serve as the default users
for database connections in queries.

Additionally, utilize the `add_alias` flag to indicate whether aliases should also be created
for the fields.
These aliases are essential for data marshaling when processing database fetch results,
ensuring seamless mapping between database fields and application-level models.
